<article>
  <h3 class="mt-5">Create a Rails App</h3>
  <p class="w-75">Open terminal and navigate to the folder where you want to create the app.</p>

<pre class="bg-light px-3"><code><span class="badge badge-secondary float-right mt-2">TERMINAL</span>
$ rails new my_new_app      <span class="comment"># creates an app named 'my_new_app'</span>
...

$ cd my_new_app             <span class="comment"># navigate in to the app folder</span>
$ bundle install            <span class="comment"># install gems</span>
...

$ rails db:migrate          <span class="comment"># create and migrate the database</span>
...

$ rails server              <span class="comment"># launch a local server</span>
...

</code></pre>

<p>Go to <code>http://localhost:3000/</code> and you should see something like below.</p>

<!-- Image trigger modal -->
<%= image_tag("rails_success.jpg", class: "img-fluid p-3 shadow", :data => { :target => "#railsSuccessModal", toggle: "modal" }) %>

<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="railsSuccessModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-xl" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h5 class="modal-title" id="exampleModalLabel">Rails Success Message</h5>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
          <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <%= image_tag("rails_success.jpg", class: "img-fluid") %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

</article>
